WEEK 3 – LAB ACTION PLAN (Collaborative Coding, Conflicts & Patch)
1. Creating an Organization (GitHub)
Step 1: Go to GitHub → New Organization → Create a free organization.
Step 2: Enter organization details → Next.
Step 3: Add members → they accept the invite.
Step 4: Set access permissions:
    Settings → Member privileges → Base permissions → Write
    Projects base permissions → Write
Step 5: Create repository inside organization (private recommended).
2. Sharing Repository with Collaborators
Steps for Collaborator 1:
- Go to repository → Settings → Collaborators
- Add people → Collaborator 2 accepts the invitation

Steps for Collaborator 2 (Git commands):
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email you@example.com
git remote -v
git clone https://github.com/username/repository-name.git
cd repository-name
git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name
git add .
git commit -m "Add descriptive commit message"
git push origin feature/your-feature-name

Keeping branch updated:
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git checkout feature/your-new-feature
git merge main
3. Forking and Pull Requests
1. Visit public repo (Person1).
2. Click Fork → repo copies to Person2.
3. Clone the fork:
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/awesome-project
4. Make changes:
   git add .
   git commit
   git push origin main
5. Create Pull Request → Person1 reviews → Merge Pull Request
4. Resolving Merge Conflicts
Step 1: Check conflicts
git status

Step 2: Open conflicted file (shows <<<<<<<, =======, >>>>>>> markers)

Step 3: Edit manually (choose/merge both versions) and remove markers.

Step 4:
git add filename.txt

Step 5:
git commit
(Or: git rebase --continue)

To cancel merge:
git merge --abort
5. Creating and Applying Patches
1. Clone any public repo.
2. Edit file → git add → git commit.
3. View commit hash:
git log
4. Create patch:
git format-patch -1 <commit-hash>
(Produces: 0001-commit-message.patch)
5. Send patch to owner.

Owner applies patch:
git apply my-changes.patch
OR (for format-patch files):
git am 0001-commit-message.patch
